@node "Document_6" "Bugs"
@{b}
 \\  \\/  /
  \\ ## /
   ####
--######--                          @{fg shine}Bugs@{fg text}
   ####
  / ## \\
 /      \\
@{ub}
None known.

There is, however, now documented undocumented feature. You can use pattern
matching for filetypes in AS option, as well as in ALIAS configuration
option. Not that it is too useful...

Also, it is completely possible to create chained ALIAS-es which would make
Action to scan for filetypes forever, for example:

.html		"HTML document"		ALIAS text/html
text/html	"HTML document"		ALIAS .html

It is also possible to use Action as your command for action on filetypes
(which isn't completely senseless, if you want to use same program for
editing and viewing filetype). That would make Action to load itself forever,
for example:

.html		"HTML document"		Action VIEW %s AS .html

@endnode
